I work down the street and was looking for a good place for lunch to grab a bite that wasnt a burger spot. Shawarma sounded great. Yafa is a quick lunch counter style place that gets you in and out. The staff is nice and keeps the line moving. I got a rice bowl with lamb and added hummus and other vegetables. Very tasty and filling. I would go back. Only draw backs were the food could have been a little warmer and they charged for the pita bread (whole piece) which I thought came with it. Out the door my meal was $11 and change.

I wasn't very impressed with the food here, in fact I didn't even finish all of my plate because it just lacked flavor.  I had opted for half lamb and half chicken and got a bunch of sides and toppings.  Overall, it's not a place I'd go back to.  The chicken was tender, slight flavor, but the lamb shawarma lacked a lot of the flavor profiles you'd expect in mediterranean food and it was still game-y.  I miss the shawarma back on the west coast and NYC!  It was so delicious there!  Overall, this place was just okay, I'm still on the hunt for the best shawarma in DC!

I went through a shwarma phase but then I let go of red meat and I never really cared for chicken shwarma so that ended phase.  But wait there's falafel.  Yafa Grille is right by the McPherson Square Metro, in the cut so you may miss it.  Everyone working there is nice and helpful as far explaining what is what and how it tastes.  I like the wide selection things that you can add to your wraps or bowls, I stick with falafel a.k.a. the script.  Another thing that I like is the fires.  They aren't those cheap, red tinged fries that a lot of places that sell gyros have.  These are much better and ask for one of the sauces in a cup for your dipping pleasure.

Surprisingly disappointed in the food - completely lacking in flavor. I ordered the hummus, added steak schawarma, with a side of falafel - my go-to for Lebanese. My pita was huge and warm and I could tear it myself to make pockets so that was fun. Honestly, though, I will not be returning because it was all so bland - the hummus was lacking any bright tones of lemon or garlic, the falafel had some mild garlic flavor but was missing the complexity of the other traditional spices (coriander, cumin, pepper, etc.) and the schawarma kind of made me feel sick - it was heavy with grease and lacking any of the flavor I'm used to with beef schawarma: a hint of vinegar and lemon and plenty of blended spices. I will say the service was good and it was cool to see them get a massive bowl of batter out of the fridge and make my falafel from scratch.

Nice little place nestled under McPherson Metro - limited menu of salads, wraps and pitas.  If they expand selection, 5 stars for what it is.  You will be pleased with the wraps.  While the meat filling of steak or chicken is very good, or perhaps falafel, the gem of Yafa Grille is the veggie toppings.  There are nearly 2 dozen to choose from and  they are all fresh and flavorful.  You can nearly taste every veggie distinctly. The meat is almost a side thought but DO get a meat as all veggie is no cheaper.  Very tasty, you will leave happy -wraps are good and large, try it!

So we finished our work went back to the metro and we stopped there for a bite . Man honest to say it was the best shawarma i had in such a long time since i was back in my country Iraq. Yafa Grill is the Chipotle for Middle Eastern food located off of Franklin Square Park in downtown DC. They serve the downtown worker community. It's a small shop (though, they have a few tables inside for dining in).  You walk in and go down the line. Choose your base (rice, salad, or wrap). Then pick your meat, toppings, sides, and dressing. Grab a large baklava if you're into sweets.  I ordered a chicken swarma wrap and it was HUGE and tasty (I'm talking about the wrap...get your mind out of the gutter!). It's also not super expensive so it's a good deal for the price you pay. They have a variety of drink options. The only thing I didn't love was their baklava. It was a little dry and not as flavorful as you'd expect.  Yafa is a really good option for a group lunch or take out.
